trans-unit.source: Storage Analytics Log Format
trans-unit.target: Storage Analytics Log Format

trans-unit.source: Each log entry conforms to a standard log format that is determined by the version of Storage Analytics Logging.
trans-unit.target: Each log entry conforms to a standard log format that is determined by the version of Storage Analytics Logging.

trans-unit.source: The first field in a log entry always specifies the version number.
trans-unit.target: The first field in a log entry always specifies the version number.

trans-unit.source: Consumers of logging data can take a dependency on this field as well as the following aspects of a log entry:
trans-unit.target: Consumers of logging data can take a dependency on this field as well as the following aspects of a log entry:

trans-unit.source: All fields, populated or empty, will be separated by a semicolon “;”
trans-unit.target: All fields, populated or empty, will be separated by a semicolon “;”

trans-unit.source: Each log entry is separated by a newline character “\n”
trans-unit.target: Each log entry is separated by a newline character “\n”

trans-unit.source: The last field in the entry will not end with a semicolon “;”
trans-unit.target: The last field in the entry will not end with a semicolon “;”

trans-unit.source: Always check the version before processing a log entry.
trans-unit.target: Always check the version before processing a log entry.

trans-unit.source: Any field that may contain a quote (“), a semicolon (;), or a newline (\n) is HTML encoded and quoted.
trans-unit.target: Any field that may contain a quote (“), a semicolon (;), or a newline (\n) is HTML encoded and quoted.
